name: YES Public 154cm
description:
The Public is completely redesigned this year – wide and blunt nose shape allows for stable, confident nose presses and a solid surface to (n)ollie from. Flat (or zero) camber keeps the board neutral enough to not get hung up without being too squirrely. The core profile has mid-flex with a slight increase in thickness just outside the binding area before tapering back down, creating a balance between softer overall flex and good pop.

-SHAPE: True Twin
-BASE PROFILE: Flat (zero camber)
-OUTLINE: True Twin, Radial
-CORE: CORE1. Wood composite with Poplar Stringers
-GLASS: Biax Top & Bottom
-BASE: Die-cut extruded 4400

name: YES Jackpot 158cm
description:
It’s a tough job to improve on a Goodwood winning ride. The Jackpot features a True-Twin outline with 2 very subtle bumps along each rail to keep it tracking across icy pipes and sketchy in-runs. We’ve kept the much-loved Camrock base profile but updated the core to a durable Poplar assembly with Beechwood impact blocks under the feet.

-SHAPE: True twin
-BASE PROFILE: Twin CamRock
-OUTLINE: Twin + Tragna Maction
-CORE: 2X Poplar + Beech
-GLASS: Triax
-BASE: Sintered, Die-Cut Base

name: YES TDF 155cm
description:
The TDF is a truly skate-influenced twin and our only true cambered board in the line-up. This year we’ve included regular width boards and refer to the original ones as narrow (N). Same twin shape as last year with an updated, lightweight core using two species of poplar with beech compression blocks in the binding area.

-SHAPE: True Cambered Twin
-BASE PROFILE: 4mm Camber, No rocker
-OUTLINE: True Twin, Radial Sidecut
-CORE: Core 3. Two densities of Poplar with Beech Impact Blocks
-GLASS: Triax top , Biax bottom
-BASE: Die-cut sintered 2000

name: Etnies Nathan Williams Brake Shoe
description:
Triple-stitched toe overlay for durability.
Midsole arch EVA shank provides extra protection from pedals without sacrificing pedal feel.
Softer EVA on toe and heel provide extra flexibility and comfort.
STI Foam Level 1 cushioning footbed for support.
BMX-specific cupsole with more durable rubber on toe and heel.
Herringbone pedal-grip tread pattern releases when needed without tearing.
Nathan Williams worked closely with the design team to create his etnies Brake shoe; exactly what he and all the brakeless BMX riders need. The Nathan Williams Brake is a cupsole with a dual durometer rubber outsole that provides more durability so the rider doesn�t wear through it. This BMX-specific outsole features a herringbone tread pattern designed to grip pedals, but also releases when needed without tearing. A dual-density EVA shank in the midsole arch provides extra protection from the pedals without sacrificing pedal feel, while softer EVA on the toe and heel provide extra flexibility and comfort. It also has a triple-stitched overlay toe for durability and an STI Foam Level 1 cushioning footbed for support. Whew! That�s a lot of features in one pair of shoes!

Learn more here...The etnies Rainforest is Coming...
For every pair of Jameson 2 Eco shoes made, etnies will plant a tree in the rainforest.
Much of the Earth's rainforests have been destroyed for farming over the last 80 years, and etnies is going to help reverse deforestation one pair of shoes at a time by planting trees in the La Reserva Forest in Costa Rica. The rainforests help curb global warming by providing more than a quarter of the oxygen to the world, and are home to hundreds of species of animals.
For more information on the La Reserva forest, visit lrff.org.

Available in 157cm size
